d 'ISHERE': module to insert markers in log files for report generation
d
d      The name ishere draws inspiration from a long-standing
d convention in academic and	technical writing:  the humble
d placeholder note like "Table 1 goes here" or "Figure	  inserted
d here." For decades, researchers have used such phrases to mark
d where results    should appear in a manuscript—especially when
d figures and tables are generated separately	 from the main
d text.    In the world of reproducible research with Stata, a
d similar need arises: how do you tell	  your analysis script,
d "Put the graph right here in the log," so that it can later be   
d cleanly converted into a polished report? The answer is ishere.  
d  Literally meaning "insert something here, on this line, in this
d do-file," ishere acts as a	dynamic, executable placeholder. It
d is a dual-purpose command designed to work with tohtml    for
d generating formatted HTML reports from Stata log files. 
d
d KW: data management
d KW: markers
d KW: Markdown
d KW: HTML
d
d Requires: Stata version 17
d
d Distribution-Date: 20260427
d
d Author: Kerry Du, School of Management, Xiamen University
d Support: email kerrydu@@xmu.edu.cn
d
d Author:  Huanyu Jia,  School of Business, Zhengzhou University
d Support: email jiahuanyu@@zzu.edu.cn
d
f ishere.ado
f ishere.sthlp
